Name: 1_guidance_organizations_quality_methods
Representative_Docs: ['iso/iec 5259-52 provides data quality governance framework for analytics and machine learning to enable the governing bodies of organization to direct and oversee the implementation and operation of data quality measures management and related processes with adequate controls throughout the dlc model according to iso/iec 5259-1', 'iso/iec 5259-4 provides general common organizational approaches regardless of type size or nature of the applying organization to ensure data quality for training and evaluation in analytics and ml', 'iso and iec maintain terminology databases for use in standardization at the following addresses iso online browsing platform available at iec electropedia available at 3.1 data life cycle life cycle of data stages in the process of data usage from idea conception to its discontinuation 3.2 data originator party that created the data and that can have rights note to entry data originator can be an individual person']

Name: 3_quality_characteristics_measures_dataset
Representative_Docs: ['key data life cycle for analytics and ml see 5.3 figure example of applying data quality characteristics from iso/iec 5259-2 in figure the data user has selected six data quality characteristics based on data quality requirements for their data quality model out of all the data quality characteristics defined in iso/iec 5259-2', '5.2.2 data quality management 5.2.2.1 data quality model for the purposes of this document data quality model is defined set of data quality characteristics which provides framework for specifying data quality requirements and evaluating data quality', 'data quality reports can include intended use of the dataset data quality thresholds relative to the organization needs and requirements for the dataset data quality characteristics selected for the data quality model explanations for specific data quality characteristics not included in the data quality model data quality measures used for each data quality characteristic results of data quality measurements data quality trends e.g']

Name: 5_step_engineer_data_quality
Representative_Docs: ['step when the data quality meets data quality requirements data engineer finalizes the data pipeline', 'for this step data engineer service developer analyses the service requirements and derives the data requirements from them step data quality manager creates data quality model for the data requirements step data engineer accesses data lake and retrieves usable data according to the data requirements step data engineer processes data into the form required for deep learning including data quality enhancement step data engineer chooses trains and evaluates model step service developer implements and launches the service and evaluates its effectiveness', 'for this step system engineer implements the functions for collecting user event data step data quality manager creates general-purpose data quality model for the collected dataset step data engineer builds pipeline to preprocess data including data cleaning etl and segmenting into time units and storing them in data warehouse step data quality manager data engineer implements the measurement functions for each data quality characteristic based on the data quality model created in step and adds the functions to the pipeline step data warehouse data quality management system reports the data set quality evaluation results step if the assessed data quality does not meet the data quality requirements data quality manager analyses the cause and suggests plan to improve the data quality step data engineer modifies the data pipeline to reflect the plan created in step']

Name: 6_provenance_information_governance_records
Representative_Docs: ['data provenance records can be used to gather and maintain data provenance information which can provide basis for determining whether the data have been intentionally manipulated or altered', 'note for more information on data provenance records see iso/iec 8000-120', "source iso/iec 3.3.3 3.15 data quality management coordinated activities to direct and control an organization with regard to data quality 3.5 source iso 8000-2:2020 3.8.2 3.16 data governance governance of data system by which the current and future use of data is governed 3.17 data provenance provenance information on the place and time of origin derivation or generation of dataset proof of authenticity of the dataset or record of past and present ownership of the dataset source iso/iec 11179-33:2023 3.11 modified the term `` data provenance '' added as preferred term definition revised"]
